title: Boyd, Mobley, Greene contributing for Georgia State
text:
Boyd, Mobley, Greene contributing for Georgia State 
Three former Colquitt County players contributed for Georgia State on Saturday in a 41-33 loss to Liberty University. 
Gabe Mobley started at center; Todd Boyd caught four passes for 38 yards; and Marquan Greene returned two kickoffs for 29 and 22 yards. 
The Panthers, now 1-3, will play host to Appalachian State at 3:30 p.m. on Saturday in the Georgia Dome. 
Of this and that: 
• Colquitt County quarterback Chase Parrish’s two touchdown passes against Lowndes on Friday give him 45 for his career. Only Reggie Stancil, with 53, has more. 
Parrish also has thrown for 3,960 yards in his career, ranking him behind Tyler Brown, who had 6,197; Stancil, 4,376; and Cole Segraves, 4,351. 
• Colquitt County is ranked No. 5 in the nation in the USA Today High School Top 25. MaxPreps has the 6-0 Packers ranked No. 7. 
ScoreAtlanta has Colquitt County ranked No. 1 in Georgia’s Class . 
• Sharmaine Washington and Tim Sanders each had nine tackles, but they were not enough as Valdosta State lost to North Alabama on Saturday in its Gulf South Conference opener. Six of Washington’s tackles were solos. 
The Blazers will play at West Georgia on Saturday. 
• Bull Barge started at middle linebacker for South Alabama on Saturday in the 24-18 victory over Troy in its Sun Belt Conference opener. 
The Jaguars, now 3-2 overall, will be off on Saturday and will meet Arkansas State at home on Tuesday, Oct. 13. 
• Johnny Ward had two solo tackles and two assists for South Florida in the Bulls 24-17 loss to Memphis last Saturday at Raymond James Stadium in Tampa. 
The Bulls will be back home on Saturday to play host to Syracuse. 
• The University of Central Florida fell to 0-4 last Saturday with a 45-31 loss to Tulane in New Orleans. 
Jamiyus Pittman had an 11-yard sack for the Knights, who will be at home on Saturday to face Connecticut. 
• Sihiem King had a kickoff return for 22 yards in Kentucky’s 34-27 overtime victory over Eastern Kentucky on Saturday. 
The Wildcats, now 4-1 overall and 2-1 in the SEC, will play host to Auburn on Thursday, Oct. 15. 
• Northwest Mississippi Community College is 6-0 after defeating Hines 42-40 last Saturday, a game in which former Packer Javonta Woods had a solo tackle. The Rangers will play at Mississippi Delta on Saturday. 
• The four teams on the non-Region 1- portion of Colquitt County schedule split their games on Friday. 
North Gwinnett lost to Norcross 38-10 and falls to 2-4; Plant High beat Wharton 40-17 to raise its record to 4-2; Shelton Felton’s Crisp County Cougars shut out Albany and are now 2-4; and Enterprise lost to Lee 21-7 and also is 2-4. 
Pelham was off last week. 
• Gilmer County, where Zach Grage is the head coach, fell to Ridgeland 31-6 on Friday for its fourth loss in a row after opening with a 29-26 win over Fannin County. The Bobcats, who are 0-2 in Region 7-AAAA, will play at Northwest Whitfield on Friday.
